  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Go not forth into the field,.... Either for pleasure, or for business; to take a walk in it for the air, or to till it, plough, sow, or reap; but keep within the city and its walls, there being danger: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor walk by the way; in the high road from Jerusalem, to any town or village near it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "for the sword of the enemy: or, \"because there is a sword for the enemy\" (b); or, \"the enemy has a sword\"; and that drawn; the enemy is in the field, and in the ways, and there is no escaping him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and fear is on every side; all round the city, being encompassed by the Assyrian army: or, the enemy's sword \"is fear on every side\" (c); causes fear in all parts round the city. The Targum is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"because the sword of the enemy kills those who are gathered round about;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or on every side. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(b)   \"quoniam gladius est inimico\", Munster, Vatablus, Junius & Tremellius; \"quia (ibi) gladius (qui) hosti\", Schmidt. (c) Gataker. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(b)   \"quoniam gladius est inimico\", Munster, Vatablus, Junius & Tremellius; \"quia (ibi) gladius (qui) hosti\", Schmidt. (c) Gataker. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
